						</div>

						<p>where <span class="equation">α &gt; 0</span> is a "regularizing" parameter to remove the noise and <span class="equation">∇u</span> is the gradient of <span class="equation">u</span>.  <span class="equation">K</span> is the out-of-focus blur.  It transforms a white point in a white circle of radius <span class="equation">R</span> such that:</p>

						<div class="equation">
							<img src="img/dissertation/theoryOfImageProcessing/eqn002.gif" alt="" />
