						<p>After processing data from each experiment, the domain contour length was plotted as a function of time, <a href="#figVIII-8">Figure VIII-8</a>.   The contour length was taken to be proportional to the total number of edge pixels in each image.   Modeling the data as proportional to <span class="equation">t<sup>n</sup></span>, where <span class="equation">t</span> is time and <span class="equation">n</span> is some exponent, these values were plotted as natural log-log and fitted with a least square fit, <a href="#figVIII-9">Figure VIII-9</a>. The fit determined the value of <span class="equation">n</span> where <span class="equation">y = y<sub>0</sub> + nx</span>.  The fits from each experiment are compared in <a href="#figVIII-10">Figure VIII-10</a>.</p>

